data.title: Endangered Species Act Of 1973
data.meta_description: Sp Plants - Free download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. This document provides information on special vascular plants, bryophytes, lichens, and fungi that are tracked by the California Department of Fish and Wildlife's Natural Diversity Database. It defines what is considered a "special plant" and describes the criteria for a plant to be included on the tracking list. The document also outlines the global and state ranking systems used by the Natural Diversity Database to assess a species' conservation status and risk of extinction within its range. Ranks run from G1/S1 for critically imperiled species to G5/S5 for secure common species.
